The coral reef biome on the sea floor comes in myriad varieties, shapes and sizes, bursting with vitality. Formed by reef-building coral and algae, this stretch of coral reef and reef animals and plants make up a fantastic community. About 'Journeys in Nature': Amazing Sansha Series Marine biodiversity is critical to the healthy functioning of the planet, and the South China Sea is home to numerous species, ranging from coral reefs to crown fish and sea lilies. Let's take a deep dive and explore some amazing creatures. For more: Amazing Sansha Series | Ep. 1: Sea lily Amazing Sansha Series | Ep. 2: Garden eel Amazing Sansha Series | Ep. 3: Crown-of-thorns starfish (Cover image via screenshot) (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)